.TH UPDATE-DISCORD-REPO 8 "February 2026" "local-apt" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
update-discord-repo \- download latest Discord package and update repository
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B update-discord-repo
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B update-discord-repo
downloads the latest Discord .deb package from discord.com and updates
the local APT repository metadata. The package is stored in the local
repository pool and can be installed or upgraded using apt.
.PP
This command uses timestamping to avoid re-downloading if the package
hasn't changed on the remote server.
.PP
After downloading, the command automatically runs
.BR update-local-repo (8)
to regenerate the repository metadata.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/lib/local-apt/pool/main/d/discord/
Discord package storage location
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns the exit status of the last command executed.
.SH EXAMPLES
To update Discord to the latest version:
.PP
.RS
.nf
sudo update-discord-repo
sudo apt update
sudo apt install discord
.fi
.RE
.PP
The command can be run periodically via cron or systemd timers for
automatic updates.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR update-local-repo (8),
.BR wget (1),
.BR apt (8),
.BR unattended-upgrade (8)
